  "local_port": 41998,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best pancake recipe that doesn't use baking powder?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a pancake recipe that avoids baking powder, you can use whipped egg whites to provide lift and fluffiness instead. Here's a simple and delicious recipe you can try:\n\n### Fluffy Whipped Egg White Pancakes\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 tablespoons sugar (adjust to taste)\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup milk (or any milk substitute)\n- 2 large eggs, separated\n- 2 tablespoons melted butter (or vegetable oil)\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)\n\n#### Instructions:\n\n1. **Prepare the batter:**\n   - In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, and salt.\n   - In another bowl, combine the milk, egg yolks, melted butter, and vanilla extract. Mix until smooth.\n   - Gradually add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, stirring until just combined. Be careful not to overmix; it's fine if there are a few lumps.\n\n2. **Whip the egg whites:**\n   - In a clean bowl, beat the egg whites with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form. This can take a few minutes. The egg whites should be glossy and stand up straight when the beaters are lifted.\n   \n3. **Fold in the egg whites:**\n   - Gently fold the whipped egg whites into the batter. Start with a small amount to lighten the batter, then carefully fold in the rest. Be gentle to avoid deflating the egg whites, which gives the pancakes their airy texture.\n\n4. **Cook the pancakes:**\n   - Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat and lightly grease it with butter or oil.\n   - Pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges look set, about 2-3 minutes.\n   - Flip and cook for another 1-2 minutes on the other side until golden brown.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Serve the pancakes warm with your favorite toppings such as maple syrup, fresh fruit, or whipped cream.\n\n### Enjoy!\nThese pancakes are light, fluffy, and delicious, making for a great breakfast without the use of baking powder.",
